staining the soil, midst of stillness.
Beloved fraternity to an end,
red eyes probe the scene. All the same, stilted for the beholder.
Depravity from the core,
handcarved death in stoneladen aisles "</i>

</center>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unekoken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nekoken</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 12:09:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> I'm of the opinion that evade is fine.  Part of the problem is so many people don't remember the old-school methods of aggro management.  Distance, delay, and turning off attack were all we used to have.  Distance is still a great aggro management tool.  Delay and not attacking are still pretty useful too (unless you are in a raid scenario where you'd best be doing as much damage in as short of time as possible.)  The old days did suck but there are valuable tactics to be taken from then.<br>
<br>
I'd rather they fixed the random number generation.  I hate failing evade like 8 times in a row because of some bad random number seed.  Just like I hate missing my backstab 6 times in a row.<br>
<br>
Narsse Nekoken of Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urunetheborrower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rune the Borrower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 12:29:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> I'm wondering if what I said about succeeding on evades 3 times in a row and never loseing agro got missed among all the post about upping the chance % here.<br>
<br>
That never happen to anyone else?<br>
<br>
No the mob wasn't rooted. I backed away and it followed me. I turned attack off for a full BS cycle before evadeing. This wasnt' CT with old world agro and yes I'm a rogue that has had his 3rd birthday about 2 weeks ago.<br>
<br>
There have been plenty of times that I've had that problem on one success but this is the first time I've seen it on three.<br>
  <p>Runehammer Trollsbane<BR>
Assassin of Cazik-Thule<BR>
<BR>
Runesword<BR>
Shadowblade of Gawain<BR>
"I yam what I yam."<BR>
Popeye</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujegredaleval.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jegred Aleval</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 1:07:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: evade success, needs upgrade, thoughts?</span><hr size=1> With every high end weapon they introduce to the game, the evade skill gets weaker and weaker, sure this is fact when you look at the weapons available when evade was first adjusted.<br>
<br>
Sure if you are good skilled you'll find a way to controll the agro, but that's not the question. Do the pokers that are available, unbalance evade ?, well hard to say, rogues are not on the 'to change list' to see anything done in the near future.<br>
Maybe when those 18 10 weapons come out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dunkelheit>Dunkelheit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 5:54:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> EVADING CASTERS</span><hr size=1> Hey guys,<br>
<br>
you really have to play a caster. <br>
<br>
While you rogues backstab for 1000 in one hit, I lay on my 553 DD and guess who gets the aggro? And what do I do without evade AND 1300 hp and 400 AC?<br>
<br>
Rogues are already the biggest damage dealers in EQ, why make evade better? So that you can even do more damage?<br>
<br>
You are calling for a chaincasting wizzie that gets no aggro at all....<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 7:09:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EVADING CASTERS</span><hr size=1> 1) I've almost never had a problem shedding aggro unless the 'tank' of the group was wearing vastly inferior gear to me, in which case I might as well tank; nothing that is even reachable by a random pickup group hits nearly hard enough to make me think the world will end if I tank it for a few rounds extra.  <br>
<br>
2) I discourage the macroing of the /doability.  I like seeing the grey buttons and knowing when I can do this-and-that next.  YMMV.<br>
<br>
3) I have exactly the opposite experience with shedding aggro on pulling.  If I pulled it, I can get rid of aggro; if I wasn't puller, I take aggro about two rounds in, and it seems to take about 2 to 5 rounds to shed.  All that says is that a few thousand hours worth of hard-wired reflexes means more than the evade skill, which I use approximately a tenth as often as people seem to think is needed.  Or it could just be Cazic Thule Redux...<br>
<br>
4) Rogue Evade seems to be about the only hate-list changing skill that still works in CT.  I can take aggro away from a warrior wielding SoD and hategiver, and then shed aggro basically at will.<br>
<br>
5) Dunkel, can it with the class flames. I'd say more, but it boils down to &quot;Class Flames are Not Welcome Here.&quot;  Technically, that goes for the rogues above you arguing about jolt and FD, too; if we don't want random trolls, we need not feed them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udarkrokshadowwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkrok Shadowwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:16:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EVADING CASTERS</span><hr size=1> He he...I completely agree with Karak on wanting to see the hide button.  <br>
<br>
That's why I have 2 keys right beside each other...my hide skill button in hotkey slot 1, and my evade macro in hotkey slot 2 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You get the best of both worlds, and if you have to turn off attack to shed agro, you have your hide button right beside your normal evade button so it's not that hard to find! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utriddletusslescruffy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TriddleTusslescruffy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 11:00:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Nekoken, I have to agree with everything you said.</span><hr size=1> I still can remember the old days where you'd just turn off auto-attack, back away and throw a couple of shirukens and then wade back in.  It was so obvious then ... turn off auto-attack or be prepared for a corpse run.<br>
<br>
I always thought it was obvious that in a pick-up group, even with evade, you have to work the aggro range with no backstabs at first just to get a feel for the main tank's taunt-ability.<br>
<br>
Sort of like diving a different car with a manual transmission, you just have to start of slowly until you find out where the sweet spot is on the clutch ... you don't just go go go <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaradinsoulcaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taradin Soulcaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 12:12:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nekoken, I have to agree with everything you said.</span><hr size=1> Hey all I have been reading through the thread and wanted to bring up the fact that the mobs you are fighting -should- have an effect on whether or not evade works.  The DPS that we output is always going to place us near the top of the hate list, it is a given.  Timing, distance, procs, and other management tools are going to help, but in my experience it completely depends on what mobs I am fighting as to my success rate on evade.. Example: Campin XP in velks @ frenzy I evade bout 80 percent of the time. Agro turns, drop it back to the tank NP. However when raiding in ToV I successfully evade bout 20-30 percent of the time. Might the mob you are fighting have an influence on your successrate? I think it does.<br>
<br>
Taradin Soulcaller<br>
58 Blackguard<br>
Ayonae Ro<br>
Exiled Alliance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufalscorpse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fals corpse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 4:02:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=40>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> about right</span><hr size=1> Every version of jolt gets resisted a LOT.  Most higher mobs you can never get Jolt to land.<br>
<br>
FD takes you out of combat longer then jolt or evade....and it gets resisted.<br>
<br>
IMO the aggro management tools handed to these three classes is about right.  You shouldnt be able massive amounts of DPS without some trade off and use of skill.  <br>
<br>
Good tanks should be a much better way to assure taking no aggro then a successful skill or a spell.<br>
<br>
Also someone mention of getting a successful evade message without shedding agro....wanted to add that happens quite a bit with Jolt as well.  Text says spell landed but mob keeps beating on ya. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 4:35:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> Distance is a factor that is more important on some mobs than others.  Example, skeleton mobs in the crypt in Seb.  95% of the agro off these is entirely proximity.  You can succeed every evade, turn attack off, beg for mercy, whatever, but if you dont move back from the mob you will get pasted.  So as for &quot;failed&quot; evades when getting a successful message, yes its very possible to evade and still have agro.  Sometimes you are just plain that high up on the list.  It also depends how well taunt works on the mob, etc.  These factors vary from mob to mob.<br>
<br>
I dont know that I agree that delay affects agro all that much.  Maybe a little but certainly not to any great extent.  Most warriors are now claiming that 2hs is out-taunting their dual wields, procs aside.  I myself used FESS and CoL for quite a while (17 dly mainhand, 18 offhand with 41% haste) and never noticed any significant agro increase over say Rage and RSSS (25 and 26 dly) even though I was hitting MUCH more and doing quite a bit more damage.<br>
<br>
Tobie Baine<br>
Assassin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevertorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evertorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 4:44:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/pmelvin14/safehousepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> Tobyl,<br>
Just wanted to correct something you stated..<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> yes its very possible to evade and still have agro.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
From a Rogues stand point, with our Evade skill, this is not true.  It's  coded that when we have a successful evade, that we drop between the 2nd and 3rd position on the hate list or 500 points, which ever is greater.  Which means that from Verants own words, there should never be a successful-failed evade.  (Assuming that the mob isn't rooted, or proximity agro, etc) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 6:47:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> There is more to aggro than just the hate list.  Evade affects the hate list.  Therefore, although evade has a substantial effect on aggro, it is not a sole determining factor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvagabond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vagabond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:19:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=44>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> This might be taken as flamish, but I don't mean it to be.<br>
<br>
Those of us that are talking about evade not being effective enough at once every 10 sec arn't just 5th lvl twinks or the like.  And we all know the _workarounds_ for evade failing.  We know about undead aggro, root aggro, etc.<br>
<br>
The person that mentioned the RNG hit it right on the head. IF VI didn't have such a crappy RNG then evade would problably be fine.  66%ish chance of succeeding is fine using any weapon combination out there, assuming your tank has comperable (and really, on raid situations, your MT always has comperable or better) weaponry IF you don't get a bad RNG seed.<br>
<br>
But VI's RNG sucks. And so we deal with evade fail after fail.  We turn off attack (often before we even get aggro), we back off.  We watch our DPS plummet.  And when we finally get a success, we wade back into the fight.<br>
<br>
The other day in an exp group, I failed evade _6_ times in a row.  Not interupted, but pure fails.  Now, this was exp, and the cleric simply chealed me after the mob and didn't think anything of it.  But the odds, given a real RNG, of someone failing evade 6 times in a row? 1:729. And no, failing 6 times in a row is not a 1 in 729 attempts event for me.<br>
<br>
If only I could find a casino that used VI's RNG, I'd be rich in very short order.<br>
<br>
Ninen of Saryrn<br>
